abstract: Former Pakistani cricket star Imran Khan leads anti-government rally in Lahore, Pakistan, attracting huge crowd estimated at more than 100,000 people; assails governing leaders and criticizes Pakistan's alliance with the United States; political analysts speculate rally is sign Khan is emerging as serious challenger to governing Pakistan Peoples Party and its longtime rival, Pakistan Muslim League-N.
snippet: A rally of about 100,000 people represented what supporters and some analysts called the emergence of Imran Khan, a former cricket star, as a serious political challenger.
lead_paragraph: A rally of about 100,000 people represented what supporters and some analysts called the emergence of Imran Khan, a former cricket star, as a serious political challenger.

headline.main: Political Shift Seen in Rally in Pakistan

headline.seo: Ex-Cricket Star Leads Big Antigovernment Protest in Pakistan
